{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, CodeBERT [180] is meticulously trained on programming languages to proficiently comprehend and generate code, whereas SciBERT [58] is tailored for parsing scientific publications and biological sequences, addressing the unique challenges of academic and medical research.",
    "Following this, reinforcement learning from human feedback (RLHF) [9] introduces a novel fine-tuning approach where models are adjusted based on rewards derived from human feedback rather than traditional labels.",
    "This method significantly aligns model outputs with human values and preferences, essential for applications demanding high engagement and accuracy in user interactions.",
    "Lastly, in-context learning [181], especially effective in models like GPT, leverages the model's capacity to generalize from a few examples.",
    "By presenting models with specific examples of the desired task at inference time, they dynamically adapt their responses to the context, enhancing their flexibility and utility without the need for additional training."
  ]
}